  "instructions": [
    "heat ghee or canola oil in a large pan over medium heat.",
    "add chopped onion and saut\u00130 until translucent.",
    "add grated ginger and green chili, saut\u00130 for 1 minute.",
    "add udtu masala, chili powder, and tagliatelle, stir well to coat.",
    "pound the mixture gently to tenderize the tagliatelle.",
    "cook for 2-3 minutes or until tagliatelle is slightly tender.",
    "meanwhile, in a separate pan, heat dash broth over low heat.",
    "when tagliatelle is cooked, add it to the broth, stir gently to combine.",
    "stir in yogurt, chopped cilantro, and crumbled papadum.",
    "season with salt to taste."
